This program was done as part of my internship at WiSilica Pvt. Ltd. at Kakkanad, Ernakulam from May to June 2019.
I had worked under the Embedded Systems department of WiSilica under a project dealing with smart lighting and IOT.
My work was to read images, scale them to desired dimensions, find RGB values of all the pixels and write it to a file and save the scaled image to a location.
The generated file was to be uploaded in the company cloud in JSON format.
The language used was C and was done in Linux environment.

Knowledge needed to complete this project:
1 - Basic C Programming
2 - Working with Files in C
3 - Command Line Arguments in C/C++
4 - Basic Image Processing knowledge
5 - About LibGD 2.2.5 - Graphics library
